This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on September 30, 2016. The memorandum delegates authority to the Secretary of State and the Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development (USAID) regarding the Global Food Security Act of 2016. The Administrator of USAID is delegated the functions and authorities of the President outlined in sections 5, 6(c), and 8(a) of the Act. The Secretary of State and the Administrator of USAID are delegated the functions and authorities of the President outlined in section 6(a) of the Act. These functions and authorities are to be exercised in accordance with the Secretary of State's responsibility for supervision and direction of assistance programs and coordinating U.S. assistance. The memorandum also states that any reference to the Act in the memorandum includes any future act that is the same or substantially the same. Finally, the Secretary of State is authorized and directed to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.